**Main flow**

1. The employee logs in to the intranet portal and selects the link to the Vacation Tracking System (VTS).
2. VTS retrieves the employee‚Äôs vacation history and balances (past 6 months and up to 18 months in the future).
3. The employee chooses a vacation category with a positive balance (e.g., annual leave).
4. The system displays a calendar to help the employee choose vacation dates.
5. The employee selects dates and hours, adds a title and short description, then submits the request.
6. The system validates the data: if errors exist, they are highlighted for correction.
7. The employee can correct errors or cancel the request.
8. If validation passes, the request is saved. If manager approval is required, an email is sent to the manager.
9. The request status becomes ‚ÄúPending Approval.‚Äù
10. The manager receives an email and clicks the link to open the pending request in the VTS.
11. The manager authenticates if needed.
12. The manager views both personal requests and those awaiting approval.
13. The manager selects a pending request, reviews details, and chooses to Approve or Reject.
14. If rejected, the manager must enter a reason.
15. An email notification is sent to the employee with the result.
16. The manager can return to the main page, approve other requests, or exit the system.

üß± Entities (Data Model)
Entity	Attributes	Description
Employee	Employee_ID, Name, Email, Department, Role, Leave_Balance	Represents an employee of the company.
Manager	Manager_ID, Name, Email, Department	Approves or rejects vacation requests.
Vacation_Request	Request_ID, Employee_ID, Start_Date, End_Date, Hours_Per_Day, Category, Description, Status, Manager_ID, Created_Date	Holds all details of each leave request.
Leave_Category	Category_ID, Category_Name, Max_Days	Represents types of leaves (Vacation, Sick, Personal).
Email_Notification	Notification_ID, Receiver_ID, Subject, Message, Status, Sent_Date	Tracks emails sent for approvals or updates.
System_Log	Log_ID, User_ID, Action, Timestamp, Details	Records all user and system activities.
